-{"id":"bd-181r","title":"Implement schema type visualization","description":"## Task: Schema Type Visualization

### Parent Feature
Phase 5: OpenAPI Display & Visual Polish (bd-urty)

### Overview
Create visual representations of JSON Schema types used in OpenAPI specs, showing object structures, arrays, enums, and nested schemas clearly.

### Background & Reasoning
Understanding request/response schemas is critical for API development. Visual schema display:
- Shows structure at a glance
- Highlights required vs optional fields
- Displays type constraints
- Handles nested structures clearly

### Technical Implementation

#### Data Structures
```rust
// crates/fastapi-output/src/components/schema_display.rs

pub struct SchemaDisplay {
    pub schema: JsonSchema,
    pub name: Option<String>,
    pub max_depth: usize,
}

pub enum JsonSchema {
    Object {
        properties: Vec<(String, JsonSchema)>,
        required: Vec<String>,
        additional: bool,
    },
    Array {
        items: Box<JsonSchema>,
        min_items: Option<usize>,
        max_items: Option<usize>,
    },
    String {
        format: Option<String>,  // email, uri, date-time, etc.
        pattern: Option<String>,
        enum_values: Option<Vec<String>>,
    },
    Number {
        format: Option<String>,  // int32, int64, float, double
        minimum: Option<f64>,
        maximum: Option<f64>,
    },
    Boolean,
    Null,
    OneOf(Vec<JsonSchema>),
    Ref(String),
}
```

#### Visualization

**Rich Mode (Object Schema)**:
```
┌─────────────── CreateUser ───────────────┐
│                                           │
│ {                                         │
│   "name": string        (required)       │
│   "email": string       (required)       │
│           format: email                   │
│   "age": integer                         │
│         minimum: 0                        │
│         maximum: 150                      │
│   "roles": array                         │
│         items: string                     │
│         enum: [admin, user, guest]        │
│   "metadata": object                     │
│         additionalProperties: true        │
│ }                                         │
│                                           │
└───────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Rich Mode (Nested Schema)**:
```
┌─────────────── Order ───────────────┐
│                                      │
│ {                                    │
│   "id": integer           (req)    │
│   "customer": {                     │
│     "name": string        (req)    │
│     "email": string       (req)    │
│   }                                  │
│   "items": [                        │
│     {                                │
│       "product_id": integer (req)  │
│       "quantity": integer   (req)  │
│       "price": number             │
│     }                                │
│   ]                                  │
│   "status": string                 │
│          enum: [pending, shipped,    │
│                 delivered, cancelled]│
│ }                                    │
│                                      │
└──────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Plain Mode**:
```
CreateUser:
  name: string (required)
  email: string (required, format: email)
  age: integer (min: 0, max: 150)
  roles: array of string (enum: admin, user, guest)
  metadata: object (additionalProperties: true)
```

### Implementation
```rust
impl SchemaDisplay {
    pub fn display(&self) {
        let output = RichOutput::global();

        if !output.should_render() {
            self.display_plain(&output);
            return;
        }

        let theme = output.theme();
        let content = self.render_schema(&self.schema, 0, theme);

        let title = self.name.clone().unwrap_or_else(|| "Schema".to_string());
        let panel = Panel::from_text(&content)
            .title(&title)
            .rounded();

        output.renderable(&panel);
    }

    fn render_schema(&self, schema: &JsonSchema, depth: usize, theme: &FastApiTheme) -> String {
        if depth > self.max_depth {
            return "...".to_string();
        }

        let indent = "  ".repeat(depth);

        match schema {
            JsonSchema::Object { properties, required, additional } => {
                let mut lines = vec!["{".to_string()];

                for (name, prop_schema) in properties {
                    let is_req = required.contains(name);
                    let req_marker = if is_req {
                        theme.style_text("(required)", "yellow")
                    } else {
                        String::new()
                    };

                    let type_str = self.schema_type_string(prop_schema);
                    lines.push(format!(
                        "{}  \"{}\": {} {}",
                        indent, name, 
                        theme.style_text(&type_str, "cyan"),
                        req_marker
                    ));

                    // Add constraints
                    let constraints = self.get_constraints(prop_schema);
                    for c in constraints {
                        lines.push(format!("{}        {}", indent, theme.style_text(&c, "dim")));
                    }
                }

                if *additional {
                    lines.push(format!("{}  ...", indent));
                }

                lines.push(format!("{}}", indent));
                lines.join("\n")
            }
            JsonSchema::Array { items, min_items, max_items } => {
                let item_str = self.render_schema(items, depth + 1, theme);
                format!("[\n{}  {}\n{}]", indent, item_str, indent)
            }
            JsonSchema::String { format, enum_values, .. } => {
                let mut s = "string".to_string();
                if let Some(f) = format {
                    s = format!("{} ({})", s, f);
                }
                if let Some(vals) = enum_values {
                    s = format!("{}\n{}enum: [{}]", s, indent, vals.join(", "));
                }
                s
            }
            JsonSchema::Number { format, minimum, maximum } => {
                let base = format.as_deref().unwrap_or("number");
                let mut s = base.to_string();
                if let Some(min) = minimum {
                    s = format!("{} (min: {})", s, min);
                }
                if let Some(max) = maximum {
                    s = format!("{} (max: {})", s, max);
                }
                s
            }
            JsonSchema::Boolean => "boolean".to_string(),
            JsonSchema::Null => "null".to_string(),
            JsonSchema::Ref(r) => format!("\: {}", r),
            JsonSchema::OneOf(schemas) => {
                let types: Vec<_> = schemas.iter()
                    .map(|s| self.schema_type_string(s))
                    .collect();
                format!("oneOf: [{}]", types.join(" | "))
            }
        }
    }

    fn schema_type_string(&self, schema: &JsonSchema) -> String {
        match schema {
            JsonSchema::Object { .. } => "object".to_string(),
            JsonSchema::Array { .. } => "array".to_string(),
            JsonSchema::String { .. } => "string".to_string(),
            JsonSchema::Number { format, .. } => format.clone().unwrap_or("number".to_string()),
            JsonSchema::Boolean => "boolean".to_string(),
            JsonSchema::Null => "null".to_string(),
            JsonSchema::Ref(r) => r.clone(),
            JsonSchema::OneOf(_) => "oneOf".to_string(),
        }
    }
}
```

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] JsonSchema enum with all common types
- [ ] Object property rendering with required markers
- [ ] Array rendering with item types
- [ ] String format and enum display
- [ ] Number constraints (min/max)
- [ ] Nested schema handling with depth limit
- [ ] $ref handling
- [ ] oneOf/anyOf display
- [ ] Plain text fallback
- [ ] Unit tests for complex schemas

